[32m│[0m `{"username":"test","user_id":10032,"user_type":"customer"}`                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Server accepts whatever user_id we submit                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Exploitation path**:                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Fuzz user_id values to discover other valid users (likely admins at low   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m IDs like 1, 0, or sequential around 10032)                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Extract dashboard content for each user - flags are often in              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m user-specific data                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Manipulate JWT user_type field for privilege escalation                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. Test wider ID ranges and edge cases if needed                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. Check additional endpoints once we have high-privilege access             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
